The paper introduces a new decision tree learning algorithm that is statistically more efficient than the current state-of-the-art. The algorithm is also naturally resilient to concept drift, which is a common problem in data mining (cs.DM) and data science (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper mentions that the algorithm can be used for classification tasks, which is a common application in computer vision (cs.CV).
